<%- include("header.ejs") %>

<style>
    body {
        font-family: 'Inconsolata', monospace;
        background-color: #f0f0f0;
        color: #333;
    }
    .container {
        width: 70%; /* Shrink the container width */
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 2rem 0;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
    }
    .about-me {
        flex: 1;
        background-color: #fff;
        color: green;
        padding: 2rem;
        border-radius: 8px;
        border: 2px solid green; /* Add green outline */
        transition: box-shadow 0.3s ease-in-out;
        box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    }
    .about-me:hover {
        box-shadow: 0 0 20px 10px rgba(0, 255, 0, 0.6); /* Green glow on hover */
    }
    .about-me h1 {
        font-size: 48px;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    .about-me p {
        font-size: 18px;
        line-height: 1.6;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    .profile-pic {
        width: 250px; /* Increase image size */
        height: 250px;
        border-radius: 50%;
        overflow: hidden;
        margin-left: 2rem;
        border: 2px solid green; /* Add green outline */
        transition: box-shadow 0.3s ease-in-out;
    }
    .profile-pic img {
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        object-fit: cover;
    }
    .profile-pic:hover {
        box-shadow: 0 0 20px 10px rgba(0, 255, 0, 0.6); /* Green glow on hover */
    }
    footer p {
        margin-left: 300px;
    }
</style>

<div class="container">
    <div class="about-me">
        <h1>About</h1>
        <p>Hey, My name is Muhammad Qasim Hassan and I developed this chat app as a practice project for Node.js and Express. This chat app is a room where multiple users can join and chat without knowing each other's identity, <br/> providing a fun and anonymous chatting experience.</p>
    </div>
   
</div>

